"{\"Course Name\": \"TECHNICAL WRITING\", \"Course Level\": \"3210\", \"Dept Abbreviation\": \"WR\", \"Course Description\": \"Cat. I. \\nTechnical writing combines technical knowledge with writing skills to communicate technology to the world. This course introduces the fundamental principles of technical communication, and the tools commonly used in the technical writing profession. Topics include user and task analysis, information design, instructional writing, and usability testing. Students learn to use the technical writing process to create user-centered documents that combine text, graphics, and visual formatting to meet specific information needs. Students create a portfolio of both hardcopy and online documentation, using professional tools such as FrameMaker, Acrobat, and RoboHelp. \\nRecommended background: WR 1010, or equivalent writing course.\", \"Requirements\": [[[\"WR\"], [\"1010\"]]], \"Is Cat 1\": true, \"Start Year For Cat 2\": -1}"